spec: hashlib_extra142
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(hashlib)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/hashlib.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/hashlib.html — Python hashlib module documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/hashlib.py"
    - "CPython source: Modules/_hashlib.c"
    - "CPython source: Modules/_blake2/blake2module.c"
    - "hashlib_extra141.zspec.zsdl — covers hashlib SHA constructor __doc__.__class__.__name__ and __doc__.__len__() / hashlib.__spec__ attribute identity / hashlib.new.__doc__.__len__()==147 / hashlib.file_digest.__doc__.__len__()==417 (table + invariants)."
    - "hashlib_extra99.zspec.zsdl — covers md5/sha1/sha224/sha256/sha384/sha512 constructor __class__.__name__ and __name__ equality / blake2b/blake2s class identity and __module__/__qualname__ / new.__class__.__name__=='function' / algorithms_guaranteed.__len__()==14."
    - "hashlib_extra98.zspec.zsdl — covers hashlib.sha3_*/shake_* constructor __qualname__ and __module__ equality / sha3_*/shake_* __class__.__name__=='builtin_function_or_method' / file_digest function identity / hashlib.__all__ class name and length."
    - "hashlib_extra97.zspec.zsdl — covers hashlib.algorithms_guaranteed membership / algorithms_available membership / new/__qualname__/__len__()."
    - "hashlib_extra96.zspec.zsdl — covers hashlib.__name__/__package__/__spec__/__loader__/__doc__ module identity / sha256/sha512/sha1/md5 __module__ cross-checks."
    - "hashlib_extra95.zspec.zsdl — covers hashlib.new/__qualname__ / sha256/sha512/sha1/md5/sha224/sha384/sha3_256/sha3_512 __qualname__ and __module__."
    - "hashlib.zspec / early extras — cover hashlib.__name__/__package__ (base spec)."
  notes:
    - "This spec does NOT duplicate invariants present in hashlib_extra95 through hashlib_extra141."
    - "Wave 281 theme: hashlib.blake2b and blake2s class constants (SALT_SIZE, MAX_DIGEST_SIZE, MAX_KEY_SIZE, PERSON_SIZE) / blake2b/blake2s __doc__ identity and length / sha3/shake constructor __doc__ lengths."
    - "hashlib.blake2b.SALT_SIZE == 16. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "hashlib.blake2b.MAX_DIGEST_SIZE == 64. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "hashlib.blake2b.MAX_KEY_SIZE == 64. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "hashlib.blake2b.PERSON_SIZE == 16. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "hashlib.blake2s.SALT_SIZE == 8. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "hashlib.blake2s.MAX_DIGEST_SIZE == 32. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "hashlib.blake2s.MAX_KEY_SIZE == 32. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "hashlib.blake2s.PERSON_SIZE == 8. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "hashlib.blake2b.__doc__ == 'Return a new BLAKE2b hash object.' (33 chars). Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "hashlib.blake2s.__doc__ == 'Return a new BLAKE2s hash object.' (33 chars). Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "hashlib.blake2b.__module__ == '_blake2'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "hashlib.blake2b.__class__.__name__ == 'type'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "hashlib.sha3_256.__doc__.__len__() == 68. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "hashlib.sha3_512.__doc__.__len__() == 68. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "hashlib.sha3_224.__doc__.__len__() == 68. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "hashlib.sha3_384.__doc__.__len__() == 68. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "hashlib.shake_128.__doc__.__len__() == 78. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "hashlib.shake_256.__doc__.__len__() == 78. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "Note: blake2b and blake2s class constants are C-level int attributes from _blake2 extension. SALT_SIZE differs between the two (16 vs 8); MAX_DIGEST_SIZE and MAX_KEY_SIZE differ (64 vs 32); PERSON_SIZE differs (16 vs 8) — reflecting the different digest widths."
    - "Note: blake2b.__doc__ and blake2s.__doc__ are both 33 chars despite the algorithm difference; both follow the pattern 'Return a new BLAKE2x hash object.' where 'BLAKE2b'/'BLAKE2s' are each 7 chars."
    - "Note: sha3_256/sha3_512/sha3_224/sha3_384 all share 68-char docstrings (sha3_ prefix adds 5 chars vs sha prefix which gives 64-66 char docs). shake_128 and shake_256 share 78-char docstrings."
